2005-06-09  TSUCHIYA Masatoshi  <tsuchiya@namazu.org>

	* nnshimbun.el (nnshimbun-request-group): Avoid multiple retrieving of
	headers.
	(gnus-group-make-shimbun-group): Use non-prefixed name when calling
	`gnus-group-read-ephemeral-group'.
	(gnus-group-make-shimbun-groups): Call `gnus-group-entry' instead of
	calling `gnus-gethash' which requires Gnus internal variable
	`gnus-newsrc-hashtb'.

2005-06-09  Katsumi Yamaoka  <yamaoka@jpl.org>

	* nnshimbun.el (nnshimbun-open-server): Remove pathname-coding-system.
	(nnshimbun-open-nov): Ditto.
	(nnshimbun-write-nov): Ditto.

	* sb-heise.el (shimbun-heise-wash-newsticker-article) Remove unused
	temp var.

	* sb-x51.el (shimbun-x51-prepare-article): Specify the boundary to
	search date.

2005-06-09  TSUCHIYA Masatoshi  <tsuchiya@namazu.org>

	* nnshimbun.el (nnshimbun-request-group): Fix message.
	(gnus-group-make-shimbun-group): Create an ephemeral group when it is
	called with the 3rd `ephemeral'argument.

2005-06-08  TSUCHIYA Masatoshi  <tsuchiya@namazu.org>

	* nnshimbun.el: Changes to enable a nnshimbun group to work as an
	ephemeral group, and several clean ups.
	(nnshimbun-server-directory): Removed.
	(nnshimbun-current-directory): Removed.
	(nnshimbun-group-prefixed-name): New inline function.
	(nnshimbun-find-parameter, nnshimbun-request-expire-articles): Use the
	above.
	(nnshimbun-group-ephemeral-p): New inline function.
	(nnshimbun-possibly-change-group): Do not make directories.
	(nnshimbun-open-server): Use `nnshimbun-address' parameter as its
	shimbun server name.  Do not make directories.
	(nnshimbun-request-group): Retrieve headers if a specified group is
	ephemeral.
	(nnshimbun-close-group): Notify that an error occurs when closing a
	group, if `nnshimbun-write-nov' returns nil.
	(nnshimbun-nov-directory): New inline function.
	(nnshimbun-nov-file-name, nnshimbun-request-delete-group): Use the
	above.
	(nnshimbun-write-nov): Do not write NOV database to a file, if a
	specified group is ephemeral.  Returns nil if an error occurs when
	writing NOV database to a file.
	(nnshimbun-generate-nov-database): Ignore group parameters,
	`prefetch-articles' and `index-range', if a specified group is
	ephemeral.

2005-06-03  Katsumi Yamaoka  <yamaoka@jpl.org>

	* nnshimbun.el (nnshimbun-default-group-level): New option.
	(gnus-group-make-shimbun-group): Use it; don't bind
	nnshimbun-pre-fetch-article.
	(gnus-group-make-shimbun-groups): New command.

2005-06-01  Katsumi Yamaoka  <yamaoka@jpl.org>

	* shimbun.el (shimbun-content-start-internal): Don't redefine it.
	Suggested by Hiroya Murata <lapis-lazuli@pop06.odn.ne.jp>.
	(shimbun-content-end-internal): Ditto.
	(shimbun-content-start): New inline function.
	(shimbun-content-end): Ditto.
	(shimbun-clear-contents): Use shimbun-content-start instead of
	shimbun-content-start-internal; use shimbun-content-end instead of
	shimbun-content-end-internal.
	(shimbun-break-long-japanese-lines): Ditto.
	(shimbun-with-narrowed-article): Ditto.

	* sb-chalow.el: Don't inherit shimbun-text, which was mis- applied and
	ineffective.
	(shimbun-make-contents): Use shimbun-content-start instead of
	shimbun-content-start-internal; use shimbun-content-end instead of
	shimbun-content-end-internal.

	* sb-f1fan.el: Don't require sb-text, though this back end still
	generates text/plain articles as before.

	* sb-japantimes.el: Don't inherit shimbun-text, which was mis-applied
	and ineffective.

	* sb-kantei.el (shimbun-clear-contents): Use shimbun-content-start
	instead of shimbun-content-start-internal; use shimbun-content-end
	instead of shimbun-content-end-internal.

	* sb-makanai.el: Don't inherit shimbun-text, which was mis-applied and
	ineffective.

	* sb-msports-nifty.el: Don't require sb-text, though this back end
	still generates text/plain articles as before.
	(shimbun-make-contents): Specify clearly the 4th arg of
	shimbun-header-insert-and-buffer-string.

	* sb-pcweb-column.el: Don't inherit shimbun-text, which was mis-applied
	and ineffective.

	* sb-sankei.el (shimbun-clear-contents): Use shimbun-content-start
	instead of shimbun-content-start-internal.

	* sb-tdiary.el: Don't inherit shimbun-text, which was mis- applied and
	ineffective.
	(shimbun-make-contents): Use shimbun-content-start instead of
	shimbun-content-start-internal; use shimbun-content-end instead of
	shimbun-content-end-internal.

